Subset the data as with Price, Mfg_Year, KM, Automatic, Weight, ABS, and Tow_Bar.

sp<- subset(ToyotaPrices, select = c(Price,Mfg_Year,KM, Automatic, Weight,ABS,Tow_Bar))

Convert categorical variables to factor type with ( yes, no ) levels.

sp$Automatic=factor(sp$Automatic)
levels(sp$Automatic)=c("NO","YES")
#NULL
sp$ABS=factor(sp$ABS)
levels(sp$ABS)=c("NO","YES")
sp$Tow_Bar=factor(sp$Tow_Bar)
levels(sp$Tow_Bar)=c ("NO","YES")

If KM is less than 500, convert the value to missing.

sp$KM[sp$KM<500]<-NA

Remove all the NA from the dataset. This will eliminate the need to tell each command to remove NA before executing.

sp=na.omit(sp)

Scatterplot matrix with factor information

Obtain a scatterplot matrix of Price, vs Tow_Bar, KM, Mfg_Year, and Weight with the points colored by the levels of Tow_Bar. Make Price the last variable. Discuss the plot. Does it appear that the relation between Price and KM is the same or different for cars with or without a tow bar? I.e., are there any clear relationships visible that appear to be different for groups of cars with or without a tow bar?

library(GGally)
ggpairs(sp, columns= c("Tow_Bar",
                       "KM",
                       "Mfg_Year",
                       "Weight",
                       "Price"),
mapping=aes(colour=Tow_Bar))

Multiple regression model

We use linear regression models to explore how the price of a car is related to the manufacturing year, kilometers and weight for cars accounting for the options abs breaks, automatic transmission, and tow bar. Save the fit to g1.

Model g1: Price=0+1Mfg_Year+2KM+3Weight+4ABS+5Automatic+6Tow_Bar+ Produce the summary table for g1. Discuss the residuals, the standard error, the degrees of freedom, R2, and adjusted R2.

g1 <- lm(Price ~ Mfg_Year + KM + Weight+ ABS+Automatic+Tow_Bar, sp)
summary(g1)

Residual plot

Obtain the residual plot with fitted values.

ggplot(g1) +
  aes(x=.fitted, y=.stdresid) +
  geom_point() +
  geom_hline(yintercept=c(-3, 0, 3), color=c(2,1,2), linetype=c(2,1,2))+
  labs(title="Toyota Prices, Model g1")

Comparing a big and a small model

Fit a model without the options variables (categorical variables). Call the model g2.

g2 <- lm(Price~Mfg_Year+KM+Weight, sp)
summary(g2)
